        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 6:04PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 604 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
East Bend, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Flat Rock...
Yadkinville...
Pilot Mountain...
East Bend...
Danbury...
Francisco...
and Sandy Ridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
